org.apache.taverna.workflowmodel.impl

Class DataflowImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.annotation.AbstractAnnotatedThing<Dataflow>
      • org.apache.taverna.workflowmodel.impl.DataflowImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Annotated<Dataflow>, Dataflow, NamedWorkflowEntity, TokenProcessingEntity, WorkflowItem

    public class DataflowImpl
extends AbstractAnnotatedThing<Dataflow>
implements Dataflow
    Implementation of Dataflow including implementation of the dataflow level type checker. Other than this the implementation is fairly simple as it's effectively just a container for other things especially the dataflow input and output port implementations.

      • link

        protected Datalink link(String sourceName,
                        String sinkName)
                 throws EditException
        Create a new datalink between two entities within the workflow
        Parameters:
        sourceName - interpreted either as the literal name of a dataflow input port or the colon seperated name of a [processorName|mergeName]:[outputPort]
        sinkName - as with sourceName but for processor or merge input ports and dataflow output ports
        Returns:
        the created Datalink
        Throws:
        EditException - if either source or sink isn't found within this dataflow or if the link would violate workflow structural constraints in an immediate way. This won't catch cycles (see the validation methods for that) but will prevent you from having more than one link going to an input port.

      • checkValidity

        public DataflowValidationReport checkValidity()
        Run the type check algorithm and return a report on any problems found. This method must be called prior to actually pushing data through the dataflow as it sets various properties as a side effect. If the workflow has been set immutable with setImmutable(), subsequent calls to this method will return the cached DataflowValidationReport.
        Specified by:
        checkValidity in interface Dataflow
        Returns:
        validation report

      • tokenReceived

        protected boolean tokenReceived(String owningProcess,
                                InvocationContext context)
        Called when a token is received or the dataflow is fired, checks to see whether the process identifier is already known (in which case we assume it's been registered and can ignore it) or registers it with the monitor along with all child entities. The method is called with the ID of the new process, that is to say the ID of the token with ':'getLocalName() appended.
        Parameters:
        owningProcess -
        Returns:
        true if the owning process specified was already in the active process identifier set, false otherwise

      • fire

        public void fire(String owningProcess,
                 InvocationContext context)
        Description copied from interface: Dataflow
        A dataflow with no inputs cannot be driven by the supply of data tokens as it has nowhere to receive such tokens. This method allows a dataflow to fire on an empty input set, in this case the owning process identifier must be passed explicitly to the dataflow. This method then calls the fire methods of any Processor instances with no input ports.
        Specified by:
        fire in interface Dataflow

      • getFailureTransmitter

        public FailureTransmitter getFailureTransmitter()
        Description copied from interface: Dataflow
        The failure transmitter contains event listeners to be notified of workflow level failures - these occur when an error bubbles up to the top of the dispatch stack in a processor and is not handled by conversion to an error token within the data stream.

        Listeners are messaged after all clean-up has been performed on the dataflow's internal state and that of any child operations within it, guaranteeing that no tokens will be generated with the id of the failed process after the message has been received by the listener

        Specified by:
        getFailureTransmitter in interface Dataflow

      • setImmutable

        public void setImmutable()
        Description copied from interface: Dataflow
        Mark this dataflow as immutable. Subsequent edits to its ports, links, merges, input and output ports will throw a RuntimeException like UnsupportedOperationException. This method should be called before executing a Dataflow with Dataflow.fire(String, InvocationContext), in order to guarantee that datalinks, port depths etc. don't change while the dataflow is running.
        Specified by:
        setImmutable in interface Dataflow
